[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426587&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426587&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

How is a user on a MILNET site that is still using Hosts.txt going to
send mail to a site that has only MF records?

There may be some way of hacking up Hosts.txt, but I can't quite see one
yet. Would making all the MF only sites aliases for their (primary)
relay site work? Can all the programs that process Hosts.txt cope with
hundreds of aliases for one machine?

